init_text:
Once upon a time there was an old mother pig who had one hundred little pigs and not enough food to feed them. So when they were old enough, she sent them out into the world to seek their fortunes. You know the story about the first three little pigs. This is a story about the 92nd little pig.

The 92nd little pig built a house out of depleted uranium. And the wolf was like, "dude."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And the 92nd little pig was like, "I mined it out of the ground".

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And the wolf was like, "that's pretty cool and all but I really meant how did you mine it from the ground?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And the wolf was like, "that is so cool!"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And the wolf was like, "can I come in and see it?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And the pig was like, "sure" and he let the wolf in.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Oh" said the wolf, "that sucks, I was really looking forward to eating you."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And the pig was like, "good riddance".

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: When the wolf was fully cooked the pig ate him.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Now Iâ€™d like to tell you about the time that the 92nd little pig single-handedly won World War Two.
